# Frontend Testing Rules

Testing stack in this repo:

- Runner: Vitest
- Component testing: React Testing Library
- Assertions: `@testing-library/jest-dom`

## Test placement and naming

- Prefer colocated tests (`__tests__` or `*.test.ts(x)`) near components/hooks.
- Keep test names behavior-focused and readable.
- Group tests by feature behavior rather than implementation details.

## Test utilities

- Reuse shared setup from `src/test/setup.ts` and helpers in `src/test/utils.tsx`.
- For Redux-aware components, use existing provider-aware render utilities.
- Mock Tauri APIs and platform-specific dependencies through existing patterns.

## Coverage priorities

- Focus on user-visible behavior and critical state transitions.
- Add tests for bug fixes to lock regressions.
- Avoid snapshot-only tests when assertions can be explicit.

## Commands

- `npm test` for standard run.
- `npm run test:watch` for local iterative loop.
- `npm run test:ui` for interactive triage.
